This paper deals with querying XML documents, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The algorithm proposed in the paper involves matching tree patterns, which is a problem that is studied in the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of the Skyline operator and the filtering of partial solutions set are techniques that are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
